[size=200][b]Discord-like Typing Indicator for mIRC[/b][/size]

A Discord-style typing indicator that shows who is currently typing in your active channel or private message, displayed at the bottom of the mIRC window using a statusbar.

[b][size=150]Features[/size][/b]

[list]
[*][b]Discord-style display[/b]: Shows "User is typing..." or "User1, User2, and User3 are typing..." for multiple users
[*][b]Real-time updates[/b]: Automatically updates when switching between channels/PMs
[*][b]Quick toggle[/b]: Press [inlinecode]F5[/inlinecode] to enable/disable the typing indicator
[*][b]Auto-cleanup[/b]: Automatically removes typing states when users part, quit, or when you close windows
[*][b]Works in channels and PMs[/b]: Tracks typing in both public channels and private messages
[/list]

[b][size=150]Requirements[/size][/b]

[list]
[*][b]mIRC[/b] (tested on modern versions)
[*][b]DCX (Dialog Control Extension)[/b] - Required for the XStatusbar functionality
[*][b]IRC server with IRCv3 typing tags support[/b] - The server must support the [inlinecode]+typing[/inlinecode] message tag
[/list]

[b][size=150]Installation[/size][/b]

[list=1]
[*]Make sure you have DCX installed and loaded in mIRC
[*]Copy [inlinecode]typing-indicator.mrc[/inlinecode] to your mIRC scripts folder
[*]Load the script in mIRC:
   [list]
   [*]Open mIRC
   [*]Press [inlinecode]Alt+R[/inlinecode] to open the Scripts Editor
   [*]Click [inlinecode]File[/inlinecode] → [inlinecode]Load[/inlinecode] and select [inlinecode]typing-indicator.mrc[/inlinecode]
   [/list]
[*]The typing indicator will automatically initialize on startup
[/list]

[b][size=150]Usage[/size][/b]

[b]Commands[/b]

[table="head"]
[tr]
[th]Command[/th]
[th]Description[/th]
[/tr]
[tr]
[td][inlinecode]F5[/inlinecode][/td]
[td]Toggle the typing indicator on/off[/td]
[/tr]
[tr]
[td][inlinecode]/test_typing <nick>[/inlinecode][/td]
[td]Test the indicator by simulating a user typing[/td]
[/tr]
[/table]

[b]How It Works[/b]

The script listens for IRCv3 [inlinecode]TAGMSG[/inlinecode] messages with the [inlinecode]+typing[/inlinecode] tag. When a user starts typing in your active channel or PM, their name appears in the statusbar at the bottom of the window.

[b]Typing states:[/b]
[list]
[*][inlinecode]active[/inlinecode] - User is actively typing
[*][inlinecode]paused[/inlinecode] - User paused typing (still shown)
[*][inlinecode]done[/inlinecode] - User stopped typing (removed from display)
[/list]

[b]Display formats:[/b]
[list]
[*]Single user: [i]User1 is typing...[/i]
[*]Multiple users: [i]User1, User2, and User3 are typing...[/i]
[/list]

[b]Automatic Behavior[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Auto-start[/b]: The indicator initializes automatically when mIRC starts
[*][b]Auto-refresh[/b]: Display updates when you switch windows
[*][b]Auto-cleanup[/b]: Clears typing states when users part, quit, or you close windows
[/list]

[b][size=150]Testing[/size][/b]

To test the indicator without waiting for real typing events:

[code]/test_typing JohnDoe[/code]

This simulates JohnDoe typing in your active channel/PM.

[b][size=150]Troubleshooting[/size][/b]

[b]Indicator not showing:[/b]
[list]
[*]Make sure DCX is properly installed and loaded
[*]Verify your IRC server supports IRCv3 typing tags
[*]Check that the indicator is enabled (press [inlinecode]F5[/inlinecode] to toggle)
[/list]

[b]Typing states not clearing:[/b]
[list]
[*]States are cleared when users part/quit or you close windows
[*]States are also cleared when users send the [inlinecode]done[/inlinecode] typing state
[/list]

[b]DCX errors:[/b]
[list]
[*]Ensure you have the latest version of DCX installed
[*]Try reloading the script with [inlinecode]/reload -rs typing-indicator.mrc[/inlinecode]
[/list]

[b][size=150]Technical Details[/size][/b]

[list]
[*][b]Hash table[/b]: Uses [inlinecode]typing_users[/inlinecode] hash table to track who is typing
[*][b]Storage format[/b]: Keys are [inlinecode]channel§nick[/inlinecode] (using chr(247) as delimiter)
[*][b]Values[/b]: Unix timestamp of when typing started
[*][b]Cleanup[/b]: Event-driven when users part/quit or windows close
[/list]

[b][size=150]Credits[/size][/b]

Created for mIRC users who want a modern Discord-like typing experience in their IRC client.

